---
const gauges = [
  { key: "mill-race", value: 24 },
  { key: "kettle-run", value: 61 },
  { key: "low-ford", value: 42 },
];
const counter = { key: "sandbags-placed", value: 120 };
const pn = { key: "earthwork-balance", fill: 74, cut: 30 };
const stockpiles = [
  { key: "spoil-north", value: 18 },
  { key: "borrow-pit-7", value: -6 },
  { key: "wash-fill", value: 12 },
];
const markers = [
  { key: "north-stake", value: "marked" },
  { key: "sluice-tag", value: "marked" },
  { key: "borrow-flag", value: "clear" },
];
const claimSlots = [
  { key: "north-levee", holder: null },
  { key: "spillway-gate", holder: null },
  { key: "pump-house", holder: "Survey" },
];
const registerSlots = [
  { key: "north-bench", atomic: "Survey", lww: "Survey" },
  { key: "gate-setpoint", atomic: "—", lww: "—" },
  { key: "pump-mode", atomic: "—", lww: "—" },
];
const pactSlots = [
  { key: "datum-grid", accepted: "Survey datum" },
  { key: "gate-policy", accepted: "—" },
  { key: "inspection-window", accepted: "—" },
];
const clients = [
  { id: "a", name: "Client A" },
  { id: "b", name: "Client B" },
];
const counterSteps = [-5, -1, 1, 5];
const pnCutSteps = [-6, -2];
const pnFillSteps = [2, 6];
---

<section id="demo" class="demo" aria-labelledby="demo-title">
  <div class="demo-head">
    <h2 id="demo-title">Photorevision, live</h2>
    <p>
      On a photorevised survey sheet, magenta marks updates not yet
      field-checked. This demo borrows that color code: pending edits are drawn
      in <strong class="k-pending">magenta</strong> and sequenced state in
      <strong class="k-seq">ink</strong>. Both clients run watershed’s real
      Gleam code in one ordered stream — map/PN/OR-map/OR-set/claims/register
      kernels plus the runtime counter channel.
    </p>
    <p class="demo-hint">
      Nudge the gauges, tally the sandbags, balance the earthwork, strike a
      stockpile, clear a field marker, stake a claim, revise a register, stretch
      the link latency, race a concurrent write. The replicas always converge —
      each structure by its own rule.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="dds-switch">
    <fieldset class="dds-picker" data-dds-picker>
      <legend class="visually-hidden">Data structure shown in both clients</legend>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="map" checked data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>Shared map</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="counter" data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>Shared counter</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="pn" data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>PN counter</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="ormap" data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>OR-map</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="orset" data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>OR-set</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="claims" data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>Claims</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="registers" data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>Registers</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="ordered" data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>Ordered collection</span>
      </label>
      <label>
        <input type="radio" name="dds" value="pact" data-dds-pick disabled />
        <span>Pact map</span>
      </label>
    </fieldset>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="map">
      <strong>Merge rule — last write wins.</strong> Race two writes to the
      same key and the op the sequencer stamps later overwrites the earlier
      one, identically on every replica.
    </p>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="counter" hidden>
      <strong>Merge rule — increments commute.</strong> Race two increments
      and both apply. The counter converges on the sum; nothing is
      overwritten.
    </p>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="pn" hidden>
      <strong>Merge rule — deltas join a lattice.</strong> Every update
      travels as a CRDT delta; merging is commutative and idempotent. Race
      it, resend it, deliver it twice — it counts exactly once, and the
      balance converges on fill&nbsp;−&nbsp;cut.
    </p>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="claims" hidden>
      <strong>Merge rule — first writer wins.</strong> A claim commits only
      if the slot is still unclaimed when the sequencer stamps it (or its
      reference SN matches the holder&rsquo;s exactly). Nothing prints
      optimistically: a filed claim is invisible — even to you — until it
      round-trips as won or lost.
    </p>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="ormap" hidden>
      <strong>Merge rule — add-wins, observed-remove.</strong> A strike only
      removes stockpile entries the striker had seen. Race a strike against a
      concurrent delivery and the row survives — with every logged yard.
      Re-opening a struck pile brings its ledger back.
    </p>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="orset" hidden>
      <strong>Merge rule — add-wins, observed-remove.</strong> Clearing a marker
      removes only the add tags this replica had observed. Race a clear against
      a concurrent re-mark and the marker remains present because the fresh tag
      was unseen by the clear.
    </p>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="registers" hidden>
      <strong>Merge rule — atomic plus retained versions.</strong> A write that
      knew the current atomic sequence wins the linearizable slot. Concurrent
      losers still append a version, so LWW reads can intentionally diverge from
      atomic reads.
    </p>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="ordered" hidden>
      <strong>Merge rule — FIFO by sequence.</strong> Adds enter the queue in
      server order. Acquires remove the front item when their op sequences; a
      racing acquire may come back empty because the earlier SN already took it.
    </p>
    <p class="merge-rule" data-merge-rule="pact" hidden>
      <strong>Merge rule — quorum acceptance.</strong> A set first prints as
      pending with a frozen signoff list. It becomes accepted only after every
      connected client signs off, or leaves drain the list.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="rig" data-demo-rig data-dds="map">
    {
      clients.map((c) => (
        <article
          class="client"
          data-client={c.id}
          aria-label={`${c.name} replica`}
          style={`grid-area: ${c.id}`}
        >
          <header class="client-head">
            <h3>{c.name}</h3>
            <span
              class="pending-count annot"
              data-pending-count
              data-live={c.id}
            >
              0 pending
            </span>
          </header>
          <table class="gauge-table dds-map">
            <caption class="visually-hidden">
              Shared map replica on {c.name}
            </caption>
            <tbody>
              {gauges.map((g) => (
                <tr data-key={g.key}>
                  <th scope="row">
                    <code>{g.key}</code>
                  </th>
                  <td class="gauge-value" data-value>
                    {g.value}
                  </td>
                  <td class="gauge-actions">
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-step="-1"
                      aria-label={`Lower ${g.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      −
                    </button>
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-step="1"
                      aria-label={`Raise ${g.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      +
                    </button>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <div
            class="counter-panel dds-counter"
            role="group"
            aria-label={`Shared counter replica on ${c.name}`}
          >
            <code class="counter-key">{counter.key}</code>
            <output class="counter-value" data-counter-value>
              {counter.value}
            </output>
            <span
              class="counter-delta annot"
              data-counter-delta
              aria-label="Pending unsequenced delta"
            ></span>
            <div class="counter-actions">
              {counterSteps.map((step) => (
                <button
                  type="button"
                  data-inc={step}
                  aria-label={`${step > 0 ? "Add" : "Remove"} ${Math.abs(step)} ${Math.abs(step) === 1 ? "sandbag" : "sandbags"} on ${c.name}`}
                  disabled
                >
                  {step > 0 ? `+${step}` : `−${Math.abs(step)}`}
                </button>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
          <div
            class="counter-panel dds-pn"
            role="group"
            aria-label={`PN counter replica on ${c.name}`}
          >
            <code class="counter-key">{pn.key} · yd³</code>
            <output class="counter-value" data-pn-value>
              +{pn.fill - pn.cut}
            </output>
            <span
              class="counter-delta annot"
              data-pn-delta
              aria-label="Pending unsequenced delta"
            ></span>
            <dl class="pn-ledger">
              <div>
                <dt class="annot">fill Σ</dt>
                <dd data-pn-fill>{pn.fill}</dd>
              </div>
              <div>
                <dt class="annot">cut Σ</dt>
                <dd data-pn-cut>{pn.cut}</dd>
              </div>
            </dl>
            <div class="counter-actions pn-actions">
              <span class="annot" aria-hidden="true">cut</span>
              {pnCutSteps.map((step) => (
                <button
                  type="button"
                  data-pn-inc={step}
                  aria-label={`Cut ${Math.abs(step)} cubic yards on ${c.name}`}
                  disabled
                >
                  −{Math.abs(step)}
                </button>
              ))}
              {pnFillSteps.map((step) => (
                <button
                  type="button"
                  data-pn-inc={step}
                  aria-label={`Fill ${step} cubic yards on ${c.name}`}
                  disabled
                >
                  +{step}
                </button>
              ))}
              <span class="annot" aria-hidden="true">fill</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <table class="gauge-table claims-table dds-claims">
            <caption class="visually-hidden">
              Claims replica on {c.name}
            </caption>
            <tbody>
              {claimSlots.map((s) => (
                <tr data-key={s.key}>
                  <th scope="row">
                    <code>{s.key}</code>
                  </th>
                  <td class="claim-holder">
                    <output data-holder>{s.holder ?? "—"}</output>
                    <span class="annot claim-note" data-claim-note></span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="gauge-actions claim-actions">
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-claim
                      aria-label={`Claim ${s.key} for ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      Claim
                    </button>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <table class="gauge-table ormap-table dds-ormap">
            <caption class="visually-hidden">
              OR-map stockpile ledger replica on {c.name}
            </caption>
            <tbody>
              {stockpiles.map((s) => (
                <tr data-key={s.key}>
                  <th scope="row">
                    <code>{s.key}</code>
                  </th>
                  <td class="gauge-value ormap-value">
                    <output data-ormap-value>{s.value}</output>
                    <span class="annot ormap-note" data-ormap-note></span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="gauge-actions ormap-actions">
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-ormap-log="2"
                      aria-label={`Log 2 cubic yards into ${s.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      +2
                    </button>
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-ormap-log="6"
                      aria-label={`Log 6 cubic yards into ${s.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      +6
                    </button>
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-ormap-strike
                      aria-label={`Strike ${s.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      ×
                    </button>
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-ormap-reopen
                      aria-label={`Re-open ${s.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      Re-open
                    </button>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <table class="gauge-table orset-table dds-orset">
            <caption class="visually-hidden">
              OR-set field marker roster replica on {c.name}
            </caption>
            <tbody>
              {markers.map((m) => (
                <tr data-key={m.key}>
                  <th scope="row">
                    <code>{m.key}</code>
                    <span class="annot orset-note" data-orset-note></span>
                  </th>
                  <td class="gauge-value orset-value">
                    <output data-orset-value>{m.value}</output>
                  </td>
                  <td class="gauge-actions orset-actions">
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-orset-add
                      aria-label={`Mark ${m.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      Mark
                    </button>
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-orset-remove
                      aria-label={`Clear ${m.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      Clear
                    </button>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <table class="gauge-table register-table dds-registers">
            <caption class="visually-hidden">
              Register collection replica on {c.name}
            </caption>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">register</th>
                <th scope="col">atomic</th>
                <th scope="col">LWW</th>
                <th scope="col">revise</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {registerSlots.map((r) => (
                <tr data-key={r.key}>
                  <th scope="row">
                    <code>{r.key}</code>
                    <span class="annot register-note" data-register-note></span>
                  </th>
                  <td class="register-value">
                    <output data-register-atomic>{r.atomic}</output>
                  </td>
                  <td class="register-value">
                    <output data-register-lww>{r.lww}</output>
                    <span class="annot register-versions" data-register-versions>
                    </span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="gauge-actions register-actions">
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-register-write
                      aria-label={`Revise ${r.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      Revise
                    </button>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <table class="gauge-table ordered-table dds-ordered">
            <caption class="visually-hidden">
              Ordered collection replica on {c.name}
            </caption>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">sheet</th>
                <th scope="col">state</th>
                <th scope="col">op</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">
                  <code>queue</code>
                  <span class="annot ordered-note" data-ordered-note></span>
                </th>
                <td class="ordered-value">
                  <output data-ordered-queue>grade-stakes, pump-check</output>
                </td>
                <td class="gauge-actions ordered-actions">
                  <button type="button" data-ordered-add disabled>Add task</button>
                  <button type="button" data-ordered-acquire disabled>Acquire</button>
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <th scope="row">
                  <code>held jobs</code>
                </th>
                <td class="ordered-value">
                  <output data-ordered-jobs>none</output>
                </td>
                <td class="gauge-actions ordered-actions">
                  <button type="button" data-ordered-complete disabled>Complete</button>
                  <button type="button" data-ordered-release disabled>Release</button>
                </td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <table class="gauge-table pact-table dds-pact">
            <caption class="visually-hidden">Pact map replica on {c.name}</caption>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">pact</th>
                <th scope="col">accepted</th>
                <th scope="col">pending</th>
                <th scope="col">op</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {pactSlots.map((p) => (
                <tr data-key={p.key}>
                  <th scope="row">
                    <code>{p.key}</code>
                    <span class="annot pact-note" data-pact-note></span>
                  </th>
                  <td class="pact-value">
                    <output data-pact-accepted>{p.accepted}</output>
                  </td>
                  <td class="pact-value">
                    <output data-pact-pending>—</output>
                    <span class="annot pact-signoffs" data-pact-signoffs></span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="gauge-actions pact-actions">
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-pact-set
                      aria-label={`Propose pact ${p.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      Propose
                    </button>
                    <button
                      type="button"
                      data-pact-delete
                      aria-label={`Delete pact ${p.key} on ${c.name}`}
                      disabled
                    >
                      Delete
                    </button>
                  </td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </article>
      ))
    }

    <div class="channel" style="grid-area: seq">
      <div class="seq-node" data-seq-node>
        <span class="annot">Sequencer</span>
        <output class="seq-counter" data-seq-counter aria-label="Latest sequence number">
          SN&nbsp;0
        </output>
      </div>
      <ol
        class="op-log"
        data-op-log
        aria-live="polite"
        aria-label="Sequenced operations, newest first"
      >
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="flow-layer" data-flow-layer aria-hidden="true"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="demo-controls">
    <label class="latency">
      <span class="annot">Link latency</span>
      <input
        type="range"
        min="100"
        max="2000"
        step="100"
        value="700"
        data-latency
        disabled
      />
      <output data-latency-out>700 ms</output>
    </label>
    <button type="button" class="race-btn" data-race disabled>
      Race a concurrent write
    </button>
    <button
      type="button"
      class="race-btn"
      data-replay
      aria-label="Deliver the most recently sequenced delta a second time to both replicas"
      hidden
      disabled
    >
      Re-deliver last delta
    </button>
    <button
      type="button"
      class="reset-btn"
      data-reset
      aria-label="Reset all gauges to their surveyed baseline values"
      disabled
    >
      Reset survey
    </button>
    <p class="status" data-status role="status">
      <span class="stamp converged">Converged</span>
      replicas identical · nothing pending
    </p>
  </div>

  <noscript>
    <p class="demo-noscript">
      The live demo needs JavaScript — it runs watershed’s actual
      <code>runtime_core</code> counter channel plus
      <code>map_kernel</code>, <code>pn_counter_kernel</code>,
      <code>or_map_kernel</code>, <code>or_set_kernel</code>,
      <code>claims_kernel</code>, <code>register_collection_kernel</code>,
      <code>ordered_collection_kernel</code>, and <code>pact_map_kernel</code>
      in your browser. The rest of the page works fine without it.
    </p>
  </noscript>

  <p class="demo-noscript" data-demo-fallback hidden>
    The live demo couldn’t start — it runs watershed’s runtime counter channel
    and kernels as compiled JavaScript modules, and this browser didn’t load
    them. The rest of the page works fine without it.
  </p>
</section>

<script>
  try {
    const { initDemo } = await import("../scripts/demo.js");
    initDemo();
  } catch (error) {
    console.error("watershed demo failed to start", error);
    const note = document.querySelector("[data-demo-fallback]");
    if (note instanceof HTMLElement) note.hidden = false;
  }
</script>

<style>
  .demo {
    padding: var(--space-section) var(--content-pad);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }

  .demo-head {
    max-width: 68rem;
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    font-weight: 620;
    font-stretch: 118%;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    line-height: 1.05;
  }

  .demo-head p {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .demo-hint {
    color: var(--ink);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .k-pending {
    color: var(--overprint-deep);
  }

  .k-seq {
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .dds-switch {
    max-width: 68rem;
    margin: var(--space-xl) auto 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    column-gap: var(--space-xl);
    row-gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .dds-picker {
    display: flex;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    width: max-content;
  }

  .dds-picker label {
    position: relative;
    padding: 0.55rem 1.15rem;
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition:
      background var(--dur-feedback) var(--ease-out-quart),
      color var(--dur-feedback) var(--ease-out-quart);
  }

  .dds-picker label + label {
    border-inline-start: 1px solid var(--ink);
  }

  /* radio stays in the tree (focusable, arrow-key switchable), drawn by label */
  .dds-picker input {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    margin: 0;
    opacity: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .dds-picker label:has(input:checked) {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--bg);
  }

  .dds-picker label:hover:not(:has(input:checked)):not(:has(input:disabled)) {
    background: var(--surface);
  }

  .dds-picker label:has(input:focus-visible) {
    outline: 2px solid var(--overprint);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .dds-picker label:has(input:disabled) {
    opacity: 0.45;
    cursor: default;
  }

  .merge-rule {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--muted);
    max-width: 52ch;
  }

  .merge-rule strong {
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .rig {
    position: relative;
    max-width: 68rem;
    margin: var(--space-lg) auto 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-areas: "a seq b";
    grid-template-columns: 1fr minmax(11rem, 0.7fr) 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .client {
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    background: var(--bg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .client-head {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }

  .client-head h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 650;
    font-stretch: 115%;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .pending-count {
    color: var(--overprint-deep);
    transition: color var(--dur-state) var(--ease-out-quart);
  }

  /* idle stays full-strength --muted (7.7:1); magenta alone marks pending */
  .pending-count[data-zero] {
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .gauge-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);
  }

  .gauge-table th,
  .gauge-table td {
    padding: var(--space-sm) var(--space-md);
    text-align: left;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .gauge-table code {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .gauge-value {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
    text-align: right;
    color: var(--ink);
